Description: A framework for deconvolution, alignment and postprocessing of 1D
    NMR spectra, resulting in a data matrix of aligned signal integrals. The
    deconvolution part uses the algorithm described in Koh et al. (2009)
    <doi:10.1016/j.jmr.2009.09.003>. The alignment part is based on functions
    from the 'speaq' package, described in Beirnaert et al. (2018)
    <doi:10.1371/journal.pcbi.1006018> and Vu et al. (2011)
    <doi:10.1186/1471-2105-12-405>. A detailed description and evaluation of
    an early version of the package, 'MetaboDecon1D v0.2.2', can be found in
    Haeckl et al. (2021) <doi:10.3390/metabo11070452>.
